    • Method Detail

      • setFile

        public SerialTypes.BackingSpec.Builder setFile(java.lang.String file)
        Path of the file backing the virtual serial port. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is SerialTypes.BackingType.FILE.
        Parameters:
        file - New value for the property.

      • setHostDevice

        public SerialTypes.BackingSpec.Builder setHostDevice(java.lang.String hostDevice)
        Name of the device backing the virtual serial port.

        If null, the virtual serial port will be configured to automatically detect a suitable host device.
        Parameters:
        hostDevice - New value for the property.

      • setPipe

        public SerialTypes.BackingSpec.Builder setPipe(java.lang.String pipe)
        Name of the pipe backing the virtual serial port. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_CLIENT.
        Parameters:
        pipe - New value for the property.

      • setNoRxLoss

        public SerialTypes.BackingSpec.Builder setNoRxLoss(java.lang.Boolean noRxLoss)
        Flag that enables optimized data transfer over the pipe. When the value is true, the host buffers data to prevent data overrun. This allows the virtual machine to read all of the data transferred over the pipe with no data loss. If null, defaults to false.
        Parameters:
        noRxLoss - New value for the property.

      • setNetworkLocation

        public SerialTypes.BackingSpec.Builder setNetworkLocation(java.net.URI networkLocation)
        URI specifying the location of the network service backing the virtual serial port.
        • If SerialTypes.BackingSpec.getType() is SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_SERVER, this property is the location used by clients to connect to this server. The hostname part of the URI should either be empty or should specify the address of the host on which the virtual machine is running.
        • If SerialTypes.BackingSpec.getType() is SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_CLIENT, this property is the location used by the virtual machine to connect to the remote server.
        This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_CLIENT.
        Parameters:
        networkLocation - New value for the property.

      • setProxy

        public SerialTypes.BackingSpec.Builder setProxy(java.net.URI proxy)
        Proxy service that provides network access to the network backing. If set, the virtual machine initiates a connection with the proxy service and forwards the traffic to the proxy. If null, no proxy service should be used.
        Parameters:
        proxy - New value for the property.
